title: Analysis of Cardiovascular and Respiratory Health
description: This was a final project for a data science course, where we had the freedom of choosing whatever dataset we wanted, and create an interactive deployment of some kind of analysis for this dataset. What I chose to do, is create a website that allows users to compare themselves to similar athletes, so they can set a baseline to improve. Website is located Here

title: Cookin Calories
description: Performed analysis on a real dataset containing cooking recipes and presented findings on Github Pages. Cleaned data and performed exploratory data analysis, conducted hypothesis testing for univariate and bivariate distributions, and used Scikit-learn pipelines to create a predictive regression model. Github Page is located Here

title: Biomechanics of Tennis Serve Motion with Increased Ball Velocity
description: Optimized the biomechanics of a tennis serve motion to increase ball velocity and proved this by using mathematical models based on Newtonian physics and statistical data from controlled experiments. You can download the reseach paper Here.
